ion"><img src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c5/=
Pendule_schema.gif/250px-Pendule_schema.gif" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"25=
0" height=3D"304" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-file-width=3D"291" data-fi=
le-height=3D"354"></a><figcaption>Diagram of a pendulum</figcaption></figur=
e>
<p>Mathematics and physics have influenced each other over their modern his=
tory. Modern physics uses mathematics abundantly,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-137" c=
lass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics#cit=
e_note-137"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>134<span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">]</span></a></sup> and is also considered to be the motivation of maj=
or mathematical developments.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-138" class=3D"reference"><=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics#cite_note-138"><span cl=
ass=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>135<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></=
sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Computing">Computing</h4></=
div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
Further information: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Theoretical_c=
omputer_science" title=3D"Theoretical computer science">Theoretical compute=
r science</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Computational_ma=
thematics" title=3D"Computational mathematics">Computational mathematics</a=
></div>
<p>Computing is closely related to mathematics in several ways.<sup id=3D"c=
ite_ref-139" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/M=
athematics#cite_note-139"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>136<span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Theoretical_computer_science" title=3D"Theoretical computer science">T=
heoretical computer science</a> is considered to be mathematical in nature.=
<sup id=3D"cite_ref-140" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Mathematics#cite_note-140"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>=
137<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Communication technologi=
es apply branches of mathematics that may be very old (e.g., arithmetic), e=
specially with respect to transmission security, in <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Cryptography" title=3D"Cryptography">cryptography</a> and=
 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coding_theory" title=3D"Coding th=
eory">coding theory</a>. <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Discrete_=
mathematics" title=3D"Discrete mathematics">Discrete mathematics</a> is use=
ful in many areas of computer science, such as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Computational_complexity_theory" title=3D"Computational comple=
xity theory">complexity theory</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Information_theory" title=3D"Information theory">information theory</a>, =
and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Graph_theory" title=3D"Graph t=
heory">graph theory</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-141" class=3D"reference"><a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics#cite_note-141"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>138<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup=
> In 1998, the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kepler_conjecture" =
title=3D"Kepler conjecture">Kepler conjecture</a> on <a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Sphere_packing" title=3D"Sphere packing">sphere packing<=
/a> seemed to also be partially proven by computer.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-142"=
 class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics#c=
ite_note-142"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>139<span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
