sion systems</a>.</figcaption></figure>
<p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biology" title=3D"Biology">Biol=
ogy</a> uses probability extensively in fields such as ecology or <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neurobiology" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=
=3D"Neurobiology">neurobiology</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:2_143-0" class=3D"r=
eference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics#cite_note-:2=
-143"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>140<span class=3D"cite-bracket">=
]</span></a></sup>  Most discussion of probability centers on the concept o=
f <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evolutionary_fitness" class=3D"m=
w-redirect" title=3D"Evolutionary fitness">evolutionary fitness</a>.<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-:2_143-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Mathematics#cite_note-:2-143"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span=
>140<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Ecology heavily uses mo=
deling to simulate <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Population_dyna=
mics" title=3D"Population dynamics">population dynamics</a>,<sup id=3D"cite=
_ref-:2_143-2" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Mathematics#cite_note-:2-143"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>140<spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-144" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics#cite_no=
te-144"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>141<span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">]</span></a></sup> study ecosystems such as the predator-prey model, meas=
ure pollution diffusion,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEBouleau1999282=E2=80=93=
283_145-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mat=
hematics#cite_note-FOOTNOTEBouleau1999282%E2%80%93283-145"><span class=3D"c=
ite-bracket">[</span>142<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> or =
to assess climate change.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEBouleau1999285_146-0" =
class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics#ci=
te_note-FOOTNOTEBouleau1999285-146"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>14=
3<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The dynamics of a populati=
on can be modeled by coupled differential equations, such as the <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lotka%E2%80%93Volterra_equations" title=3D"L=
otka=E2=80=93Volterra equations">Lotka=E2=80=93Volterra equations</a>.<sup =
id=3D"cite_ref-147" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Mathematics#cite_note-147"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>144<s=
pan class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Statistical_hypothesis_test=
ing" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Statistical hypothesis testing">Statist=
ical hypothesis testing</a>, is run on data from <a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Clinical_trial" title=3D"Clinical trial">clinical trials</a>=
 to determine whether a new treatment works.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-148" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics#cite_no=
te-148"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>145<span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">]</span></a></sup> Since the start of the 20th century, chemistry has use=
d computing to model molecules in three dimensions.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-149"=
 class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics#c=
ite_note-149"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>146<span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
