<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Historical_dynamics" title=3D"Hist=
orical dynamics">Historical dynamics</a></div>
<p>Areas of mathematics used in the social sciences include probability/sta=
tistics and differential equations. These are used in <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linguistics" title=3D"Linguistics">linguistics</a>, <a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Economics" title=3D"Economics">econom=
ics</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sociology" title=3D"Socio=
logy">sociology</a>,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-154" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics#cite_note-154"><span class=3D"ci=
te-bracket">[</span>151<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> and =
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Psychology" title=3D"Psychology">p=
sychology</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-155" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics#cite_note-155"><span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">[</span>152<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size skin-invert-image" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Supply-demand-equilibrium.s=
