 data-file-width=3D"2048" data-file-height=3D"2048"></a><figcaption><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fractal" title=3D"Fractal">Fractal</a> wi=
th a scaling symmetry and a central symmetry</figcaption></figure>
<p>Humans, as well as some other animals, find symmetric patterns to be mor=
e beautiful.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-209" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics#cite_note-209"><span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">[</span>201<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Mathematical=
ly, the symmetries of an object form a group known as the <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Symmetry_group" title=3D"Symmetry group">symmetry g=
roup</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-210" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics#cite_note-210"><span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>[</span>202<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> For example, th=
e group underlying mirror symmetry is the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Cyclic_group" title=3D"Cyclic group">cyclic group</a> of two elemen=
ts, <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D=
