</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Popularization">Popularizat=
ion</h3></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
Main article: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Popular_mathematics"=
 title=3D"Popular mathematics">Popular mathematics</a></div><p>Popular math=
ematics is the act of presenting mathematics without technical terms.<sup i=
d=3D"cite_ref-216" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Mathematics#cite_note-216"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>208<sp=
an class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Presenting mathematics may be =
hard since the general public suffers from <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Mathematical_anxiety" title=3D"Mathematical anxiety">mathematical =
anxiety</a> and mathematical objects are highly abstract.<sup id=3D"cite_re=
f-217" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathema=
tics#cite_note-217"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>209<span class=3D"=
cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> However, popular mathematics writing can o=
vercome this by using applications or cultural links.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-21=
8" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics=
#cite_note-218"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>210<span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Despite this, mathematics is rarely the topic =
of popularization in printed or televised media.
</p><div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Awards_and_prize_proble=
ms">Awards and prize problems</h3></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
Main category: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Category:Mathematic=
s_awards" title=3D"Category:Mathematics awards">Mathematics awards</a></div=
>
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:FieldsMedalFront.jpg" class=3D"mw-file-descri=
ption"><img src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0=
c/FieldsMedalFront.jpg/250px-FieldsMedalFront.jpg" decoding=3D"async" width=
=3D"250" height=3D"240" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-file-width=3D"2493" =
data-file-height=3D"2398"></a><figcaption>The front side of the <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fields_Medal" title=3D"Fields Medal">Fields M=
edal</a> with an illustration of the Greek <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Polymath" title=3D"Polymath">polymath</a> <a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Archimedes" title=3D"Archimedes">Archimedes</a></figcaptio=
n></figure>
<p>The most prestigious award in mathematics is the <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Fields_Medal" title=3D"Fields Medal">Fields Medal</a>,<su=
p id=3D"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEMonastyrsky20011_219-0" class=3D"reference"><a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics#cite_note-FOOTNOTEMonastyrsk=
y20011-219"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>211<span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-FOOTNOTERiehm2002778=E2=80=9378=
2_220-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathe=
matics#cite_note-FOOTNOTERiehm2002778%E2%80%93782-220"><span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">[</span>212<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> establi=
shed by Canadian <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Charles_Fiel=
ds" title=3D"John Charles Fields">John Charles Fields</a> in 1936 and award=
ed every four years (except around <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/World_War_II_in_Yugoslavia" title=3D"World War II in Yugoslavia">World War=
 II</a>) to up to four individuals.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-221" class=3D"refere=
nce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics#cite_note-221"><s=
pan class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>213<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span>=
</a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-StAndrews-Fields_222-0" class=3D"reference"><=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics#cite_note-StAndrews-Fie=
lds-222"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>214<span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">]</span></a></sup> It is considered the mathematical equivalent of the <=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nobel_Prize" title=3D"Nobel Prize">=
Nobel Prize</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-StAndrews-Fields_222-1" class=3D"refere=
nce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics#cite_note-StAndre=
ws-Fields-222"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>214<span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Other prestigious mathematics awards include:<sup id=3D"cite_ref-223=
" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics#=
cite_note-223"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>215<span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<ul><li>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abel_Prize" title=3D"A=
bel Prize">Abel Prize</a>, instituted in 2002<sup id=3D"cite_ref-224" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics#cite_no=
te-224"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>216<span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">]</span></a></sup> and first awarded in 2003<sup id=3D"cite_ref-225" clas=
s=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics#cite_n=
ote-225"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>217<span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">]</span></a></sup></li>
<li>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chern_Medal" title=3D"Cher=
n Medal">Chern Medal</a> for lifetime achievement, introduced in 2009<sup i=
d=3D"cite_ref-226" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Mathematics#cite_note-226"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>218<sp=
an class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> and first awarded in 2010<sup =
id=3D"cite_ref-227" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Mathematics#cite_note-227"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>219<s=
pan class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup></li>
<li>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American_Mathematical_Soci=
ety" title=3D"American Mathematical Society">AMS</a> <a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Leroy_P._Steele_Prize" title=3D"Leroy P. Steele Prize">L=
eroy P. Steele Prize</a>, awarded since 1970<sup id=3D"cite_ref-228" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics#cite_no=
te-228"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>220<span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">]</span></a></sup></li>
<li>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wolf_Prize_in_Mathematics"=
 title=3D"Wolf Prize in Mathematics">Wolf Prize in Mathematics</a>, also fo=
r lifetime achievement,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-229" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics#cite_note-229"><span class=3D=
"cite-bracket">[</span>221<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> i=
nstituted in 1978<sup id=3D"cite_ref-230" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics#cite_note-230"><span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">[</span>222<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup></li></u=
l>
<p>A famous list of 23 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open_proble=
m" title=3D"Open problem">open problems</a>, called "<a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Hilbert%27s_problems" title=3D"Hilbert's problems">Hilbe=
rt's problems</a>", was compiled in 1900 by German mathematician David Hilb=
ert.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:0_231-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics#cite_note-:0-231"><span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">[</span>223<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> This list ha=
s achieved great celebrity among mathematicians,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-232" cl=
ass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics#cite=
_note-232"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>224<span class=3D"cite-brac=
ket">]</span></a></sup> and at least thirteen of the problems (depending ho=
w some are interpreted) have been solved.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:0_231-1" clas=
s=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics#cite_n=
ote-:0-231"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>223<span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>A new list of seven important problems, titled the "<a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Millennium_Prize_Problems" title=3D"Millennium Pri=
ze Problems">Millennium Prize Problems</a>", was published in 2000. Only on=
e of them, the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Riemann_hypothesis"=
 title=3D"Riemann hypothesis">Riemann hypothesis</a>, duplicates one of Hil=
bert's problems. A solution to any of these problems carries a 1 million do=
llar reward.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-233" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics#cite_note-233"><span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">[</span>225<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> To date, onl=
y one of these problems, the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poinc=
ar%C3%A9_conjecture" title=3D"Poincar=C3=A9 conjecture">Poincar=C3=A9 conje=
cture</a>, has been solved, by the Russian mathematician <a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grigori_Perelman" title=3D"Grigori Perelman">Grigori=
 Perelman</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-234" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics#cite_note-234"><span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">[</span>226<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
